[1] Case update
- Tue 18 Aug 2020. News scan
[CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy), abridged, edited]
https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2020/08/news-scan-aug-18-2020

One more Ebola illness and one more death from the virus have been confirmed in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) Equateur province outbreak, the World Health Organization (WHO) African regional office said on Twitter today [18 Aug 2020].

The new developments push the outbreak total to 89 cases and 37 deaths.

In its latest weekly outbreaks and health emergencies report, the WHO regional office said a healthcare worker strike was occurring in some of the affected area, including the provincial capital, Mbandaka. WHO sources and other officials said a 3-day strike over unpaid wages ended yesterday [17 Aug 2020], according to Reuters [see report below. - Mod.LK].

The WHO update also said 5 patients with confirmed Ebola infections remain in the community, posing a risk of further spread. It also noted that 30 health areas have now reported cases, although 3 have gone without a case for 42 days.

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
